long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1224042 shutdown messages
Description of problem: Mustang does not reboot/shutdown since installing kernel-4.8.8-300.fc25
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kernel-4.8.8-300.fc25 tianocore 3.06.25 (also 3.06.18)
How reproducible: Everytime
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install kernel-4.8.8-300.fc25 2. Reboot the system.
Actual results: System hangs.
Expected results: System reboots
Additional info: Also tested 4.8.8-200.fc24, kernel-4.8.10-300.fc25 same result. Working reboot/shutdown with kernel-4.8.6-300.
kernel-4.8.11-300 is the same. Upgrading to 4.9 I have not had an issue with shutdown or network connectivity(bz#1401998).

*********** MASS BUG UPDATE ************** We apologize for the inconvenience. There is a large number of bugs to go through and several of them have gone stale. Due to this, we are doing a mass bug update across all of the Fedora 25 kernel bugs.
Fedora 25 has now been rebased to 4.9.3-200.fc25. Please test this kernel update (or newer) and let us know if you issue has been resolved or if it is still present with the newer kernel.
If you have moved on to Fedora 26, and are still experiencing this issue, please change the version to Fedora 26.
If you experience different issues, please open a new bug report for those.
Not seeing the issue with 4.9, closing.
